spec_version: 0.2.0-alpha
file_type: content-entity
id: fault_lines_07_the_chasm
status: draft
implemented_in: ["src/embergrave/levels/fault_lines_07_the_chasm.py"]
name: "The Chasm"
region: fault_lines
difficulty_tier: 3
time_target_ms: 210000
entry: { x: 1500, y: 18000 }
exit:  { x: 7000, y: 2500 }
checkpoints:
  - { x: 2800, y: 11200 }
  - { x: 2300, y: 5200 }
platforms:
  - { x: 500,  y: 17500, width: 2500, height: 300, surface: solid }
  - { x: 5000, y: 14500, width: 1200, height: 200, surface: solid }
  - { x: 2000, y: 11000, width: 2000, height: 200, surface: solid }
  - { x: 5500, y: 8000,  width: 1500, height: 200, surface: one_way }
  - { x: 1500, y: 5000,  width: 2000, height: 200, surface: solid }
  - { x: 5000, y: 2000,  width: 3500, height: 300, surface: solid }
ember_pickups:
  - { x: 5500, y: 15300, ember_value: 2 }
  - { x: 3000, y: 12000, ember_value: 2 }
  - { x: 6000, y: 8800,  ember_value: 2 }
  - { x: 7000, y: 3000,  ember_value: 2 }
lethal_regions:
  - { x: 0,    y: 0,    width: 9000, height: 400,  tag: void }
  - { x: 0,    y: 400,  width: 4500, height: 800,  tag: lava }
  - { x: 0,    y: 9000, width: 400,  height: 2000, tag: spike }
  - { x: 8600, y: 9000, width: 400,  height: 2000, tag: spike }
notes: "Vertical descent through a narrow fault-line chasm. Entry at the top-left (y=18000); exit at the bottom-right (y=2500). Six platforms alternate side-of-shaft as the moth drops (~3000 micro_units between consecutive platform tops), forcing the player to read the next ledge through ember-light before committing — a tier-3 commitment puzzle, not a precision-jump puzzle. The two checkpoints sit on the third and fifth platforms (the two left-side platforms in the middle bands), breaking the ~16000-micro_unit descent into three sections of roughly equal flight count. The mid-shaft fourth platform is one_way so a missed-checkpoint route from the lower section can climb back up through it. Bottom of the shaft is a void/lava trough — the lava covers the left two-thirds of the floor so an overshoot off the final ledge dies in lava rather than void (region-appropriate kill). Spike walls in the middle band (y=9000-11000) punish lateral overshoot on a dashed descent. Four ember pickups at value 2 each (total 8) are placed off-platform between drops to reward commitment-to-route rather than refueling on the safe path; expected median ember at second-checkpoint touch ≈ 6, hitting balance_targets.ember_velocity. Tier 3: 5-15 deaths is the acceptable band; first-clear ~3.5 minutes for a skilled player."
```

