| `checkpoints` | 1–5 items | 2 items | ✓ |
| `platforms` | ≥1 item, each `{x, y, width≥1, height≥1, surface?}` | 6 items (5 solid + 1 one_way) | ✓ |
| `ember_pickups` | each `ember_value` 1–4 | 4 items × value=2 (total 8) | ✓ |
| `lethal_regions` | tag ∈ {lava, spike, void, crusher} | 4 items (void, lava, spike×2) | ✓ |

## Design-intent check against task

- **Top entry, bottom exit, vertical shaft** — entry y=18000, exit y=2500. ✓
- **Six platforms, mix of wide/narrow** — wide entry/exit (2500w / 3500w) + four narrower mid-shaft ledges (1200–2000w), with one `one_way`. ✓
- **Two checkpoints on the natural descent path** — placed atop platforms 3 and 5. ✓
- **Four ember pickups, ~8 ember total** — 4 × value-2 = 8. ✓
- **Void/lava region at bottom, falling past exit is lethal** — void floor spans full 9000 width; lava covers the left two-thirds; the exit platform sits over void on its right edge so a right-overshoot also dies. ✓
- **Tier-3 fault_lines parity with `fault_lines_03_the_drop`** — comparable shaft height, gap distances, side-spike hazards, one one_way platform for back-route recovery, similar `time_target_ms`. ✓

